00:12:42,383 --> 00:12:45,783
If we don't make money during
lunch, we've wasted half a day.

268
00:12:45,883 --> 00:12:48,953
This is why I told you we
should go in front of a school.

269
00:12:48,983 --> 00:12:51,983
They are on vacation. We
won't be making money there.

270
00:12:52,083 --> 00:12:54,983
And they said a dish like this sells
better around office complexes...

271
00:12:55,023 --> 00:12:56,753
because employees miss homemade meals.

272
00:12:56,783 --> 00:12:59,882
Is that right? Then let's
wait a little more.

273
00:12:59,883 --> 00:13:00,983
They will come.

274
00:13:03,683 --> 00:13:05,583
- Welcome. - Welcome. What can I get you?

275
00:13:11,883 --> 00:13:12,883
Sir?

276
00:13:18,583 --> 00:13:22,083
What's wrong with him? Do you know him?

277
00:13:22,583 --> 00:13:23,683
I've never seen him before.

278
00:13:24,283 --> 00:13:26,083
He's a strange one, isn't he?

279
00:13:28,583 --> 00:13:31,183
You can't sell food here.
Do you want to pay a fine?

280
00:13:31,483 --> 00:13:32,783
What do we do?

281
00:13:32,883 --> 00:13:34,983
Gosh, this is such a hassle.

282
00:13:35,783 --> 00:13:36,903
Show me your identification.

283
00:13:38,083 --> 00:13:40,683
All right. All right.

284
00:13:41,183 --> 00:13:42,383
I'm sorry.

285
00:13:42,483 --> 00:13:45,183
We didn't sell anything today
so please let this go.

286
00:13:45,283 --> 00:13:48,853
You can't sell food here.
We will get complaints.

287
00:13:48,953 --> 00:13:51,283
I am sorry. We will close now. I am sorry.

288
00:13:51,383 --> 00:13:53,183
- Please let it pass. - We are sorry.

289
00:13:53,283 --> 00:13:54,783
- I'm sorry. - Hurry up and leave.

290
00:13:54,883 --> 00:13:57,483
- Okay. - You can't block the street.

291
00:13:57,583 --> 00:14:00,283
We will move now. We didn't
even sell one bowl yet.

292
00:14:01,683 --> 00:14:02,783
Ki Beom.

293
00:14:04,253 --> 00:14:05,783
Your father still hasn't woken up.

294
00:14:06,783 --> 00:14:07,883
Yes.

295
00:14:12,353 --> 00:14:13,383
Okay.

296
00:14:16,383 --> 00:14:17,583
Why are you still here?

297
00:14:18,583 --> 00:14:19,583
Although...

298
00:14:20,623 --> 00:14:22,583
I did a terrible thing,

299
00:14:24,283 --> 00:14:25,683
I can't leave...

300
00:14:26,783 --> 00:14:28,183
President like that.

301
00:14:29,783 --> 00:14:33,383
I will stay here and repent
my sins until he wakes up.

302
00:14:34,783 --> 00:14:35,983
When he wakes up,

303
00:14:36,883 --> 00:14:38,383
I will quietly disappear.

304
00:14:39,083 --> 00:14:41,364
I can't understand why you're
doing this all of a sudden.

305
00:14:42,483 --> 00:14:44,083
When you did something like that,

306
00:14:45,083 --> 00:14:46,883
you must have known that
this day would come.

307
00:14:47,483 --> 00:14:48,583
Do Kyung.

308
00:14:49,083 --> 00:14:50,583
Please, let me meet him once.

309
00:14:51,783 --> 00:14:52,783
Please,

310
00:14:53,383 --> 00:14:54,853
let me meet him one last time.

311
00:14:55,583 --> 00:14:57,683
Meet him in your next life.

312
00:14:58,383 --> 00:15:01,083
Don't let Ki Beom catch you
and put yourself in danger.

313
00:15:01,783 --> 00:15:03,483
You should leave for your own sake.

314
00:15:13,683 --> 00:15:14,683
Goodness.

315
00:15:15,383 --> 00:15:17,083
Why are we having a barbecue party?

316
00:15:17,383 --> 00:15:20,383
For you to work in the cold,
you need to be strong.

317
00:15:20,483 --> 00:15:21,983
So you need to eat well.

318
00:15:22,083 --> 00:15:23,983
- I bought these. - Really?

319
00:15:24,653 --> 00:15:27,123
My Soo Min bought meat for us?

320
00:15:27,283 --> 00:15:30,253
How can I afford to buy meat when
I get such a small allowance?

321
00:15:30,283 --> 00:15:32,982
He bought the meat and I
bought the vegetables.

322
00:15:32,983 --> 00:15:36,483
- Gosh. - Help yourselves!

323
00:15:36,583 --> 00:15:39,853
Of course. My boy is so thoughtful.

324
00:15:40,983 --> 00:15:42,753
Let's eat. Let's eat, Mum.

325
00:15:42,883 --> 00:15:45,583
- Here. - Wow. Here.

326
00:15:45,683 --> 00:15:46,783
Let's eat.

327
00:15:46,853 --> 00:15:48,583
It looks delicious. Thank you.

328
00:15:48,683 --> 00:15:51,882
How many bowls did you sell today?
100 bowls? 200 bowls?

329
00:15:51,883 --> 00:15:54,253
Hey, it was just their first day.

330
00:15:56,883 --> 00:15:59,483
Actually, it turned out much
better than we imagined.

331
00:15:59,883 --> 00:16:01,183
Our customers went...

332
00:16:01,283 --> 00:16:03,983
wild about our fried rice. Right, Honey?

333
00:16:04,083 --> 00:16:06,753
Yes, it was very popular.

334
00:16:07,083 --> 00:16:10,253
We will settle down soon.
So don't worry about us.

335
00:16:10,283 --> 00:16:12,683
I hope it works out so that you can...

336
00:16:12,783 --> 00:16:16,283
buy me a mink coat and take me abroad, too.

337
00:16:16,383 --> 00:16:17,983
Gosh, Mum.

338
00:16:18,853 --> 00:16:21,082
Should we make a toast?

339
00:16:21,083 --> 00:16:22,982
- Okay. - Okay.

340
00:16:22,983 --> 00:16:26,253
To our health.

341
00:16:26,283 --> 00:16:28,383
- To our health. - To our health.

342
00:16:28,483 --> 00:16:30,283
Thank you. Thank you for the party.

343
00:16:33,083 --> 00:16:34,483
It's delicious.

344
00:16:36,383 --> 00:16:37,583
What's going on?

345
00:16:37,653 --> 00:16:39,183
- Come on, Dad. - What is it?

346
00:16:40,283 --> 00:16:43,283
You should get a massage. Take a seat.

347
00:16:43,483 --> 00:16:45,683
Okay. Thank you, Soo Min.

348
00:16:45,783 --> 00:16:46,853
- Goodness. - Here we go.

349
00:16:47,753 --> 00:16:50,583
- I will set it for you. - Gosh.

350
00:16:52,483 --> 00:16:53,553
Does that feel good?

351
00:16:53,653 --> 00:16:56,983
It feels very good. Goodness.

352
00:16:58,683 --> 00:17:01,853
Soo Min! Why are you being so nice today?

353
00:17:02,353 --> 00:17:04,793
- Do you need money? - No, that's not it.

354
00:17:05,293 --> 00:17:06,583
I'm always nice to Mum and Dad.

355
00:17:07,293 --> 00:17:10,083
- Right, Dad? - Of course.

356
00:17:10,793 --> 00:17:13,383
My kids are the best.

357
00:17:16,183 --> 00:17:19,183
This feels so nice. Gosh.

358
00:17:23,793 --> 00:17:25,183
Are you going over the numbers?

359
00:17:27,083 --> 00:17:30,853
Honey. We sold four bowls today.

360
00:17:31,793 --> 00:17:33,483
We were out in the cold the whole day...

361
00:17:34,253 --> 00:17:35,853
and all we earned was 16 dollars.

362
00:17:36,793 --> 00:17:39,883
When we deduct expenses, we
won't have anything left.

363
00:17:40,983 --> 00:17:43,983
The family's so excited. How
can we go on like this?

364
00:17:45,583 --> 00:17:47,683
Should we lower the price?
Is it too expensive?

365
00:17:47,793 --> 00:17:49,883
But other places charge
five dollars for a bowl.

366
00:17:50,853 --> 00:17:53,883
Maybe it doesn't taste good.
Should we change the menu?

367
00:17:53,983 --> 00:17:54,983
Gosh.

368
00:17:55,083 --> 00:17:57,983
I haven't met anyone that
didn't like your cooking.

369
00:17:59,183 --> 00:18:00,883
Then what's the problem?

370
00:18:01,683 --> 00:18:04,383
Gosh, this is only the start.

371
00:18:05,583 --> 00:18:07,483
It's not easy to do well from the start.

372
00:18:08,953 --> 00:18:10,483
It will get better.

373
00:18:10,883 --> 00:18:13,583
We will sell 10 bowls tomorrow
and 15 bowls the day after.

374
00:18:13,683 --> 00:18:16,483
Then, there will come a day
when we sell 100 bowls a day.

375
00:18:17,083 --> 00:18:20,383
Let's not expect too much for now.
We need to look on the bright side.

376
00:18:22,853 --> 00:18:26,083
You're right. I just became
anxious all of a sudden.

377
00:18:28,183 --> 00:18:29,293
It's okay.

378
00:18:44,793 --> 00:18:45,793
Ms Oh!

379
00:18:47,883 --> 00:18:51,293
Are you mad? How can you come here?

380
00:18:51,383 --> 00:18:54,183
I couldn't leave without you.

381
00:18:54,253 --> 00:18:55,483
Run away with me.

382
00:18:56,583 --> 00:18:57,683
Let's not do this.

383
00:18:57,883 --> 00:18:58,953
You and I...

384
00:18:59,293 --> 00:19:00,483
are already over.

385
00:19:03,583 --> 00:19:04,983
I thought you said you loved me.

386
00:19:06,383 --> 00:19:08,683
You even said so in front of President.

387
00:19:08,953 --> 00:19:10,483
Well, that's...

388
00:19:11,383 --> 00:19:13,683
It was so that I could save you.

389
00:19:15,683 --> 00:19:17,083
Please, don't do this to me.

390
00:19:17,883 --> 00:19:20,683
I have to stay by his side.

391
00:19:20,883 --> 00:19:22,353
You call this staying by his side?

392
00:19:22,383 --> 00:19:24,083
You can't even go inside.

393
00:19:24,183 --> 00:19:25,183
Even still,

394
00:19:26,383 --> 00:19:27,853
I can't leave like this.

395
00:19:29,753 --> 00:19:30,793
I'll regret it...

396
00:19:31,353 --> 00:19:32,683
for the rest of my life.

397
00:19:33,683 --> 00:19:34,883
I feel guilty.

398
00:19:35,353 --> 00:19:37,253
Please, wake up and smell the coffee!

399
00:19:37,293 --> 00:19:39,083
You might be in danger.

400
00:19:54,723 --> 00:19:57,453
Did you see that? Ki Beom just passed by.

401
00:19:57,553 --> 00:19:58,723
This is our reality.

402
00:19:58,793 --> 00:20:01,753
If he finds out that we're here,
who knows what will happen.

403
00:20:02,083 --> 00:20:04,982
That's why you should leave right now.

404
00:20:04,983 --> 00:20:06,083
Ms Oh!

405
00:20:06,293 --> 00:20:08,383
Please, I'm begging you.

406
00:20:09,983 --> 00:20:11,083
I'll wait for you...

407
00:20:11,793 --> 00:20:13,753
at the terminal. Meet me at 12pm sharp.

408
00:20:14,383 --> 00:20:16,453
No, don't wait for me.

409
00:20:17,983 --> 00:20:19,293
I won't show up.

410
00:20:19,353 --> 00:20:21,083
I'll wait until you do.

411
00:20:21,623 --> 00:20:23,023
I'll wait for you every single day.

412
00:20:31,293 --> 00:20:32,883
Why isn't he waking up?

413
00:20:33,983 --> 00:20:35,583
What if he never wakes up?

414
00:20:36,483 --> 00:20:37,883
Don't say that.

415
00:20:38,953 --> 00:20:40,823
The doctor came by earlier...

416
00:20:40,883 --> 00:20:42,553
and said that we need to be patient.

417
00:20:43,653 --> 00:20:44,793
Dad.

418
00:20:45,083 --> 00:20:46,683
Wake up.

419
00:20:47,083 --> 00:20:48,293
You should get back on your feet...

420
00:20:48,383 --> 00:20:50,793
and get revenge on those who betrayed you.

421
00:20:51,293 --> 00:20:52,983
Doesn't it make you furious...

422
00:20:53,623 --> 00:20:54,683
to just lie here?

423
00:21:00,183 --> 00:21:01,183
Yes.

424
00:21:02,253 --> 00:21:03,253
What?

425
00:21:03,483 --> 00:21:05,723
The tenants sent in another petition?

426
00:21:06,483 --> 00:21:09,653
Do they want to see me go crazy?

427
00:21:11,983 --> 00:21:13,483
All right. I'll be there.

428
00:21:15,823 --> 00:21:17,253
What is it?

429
00:21:17,983 --> 00:21:18,983
It's just work.

430
00:21:19,583 --> 00:21:21,823
With your dad sick,

431
00:21:22,083 --> 00:21:24,483
you really need to take the lead
and look after the company.

432
00:21:25,183 --> 00:21:28,483
You said that you don't want to be
someone who just holds the title.

433
00:21:29,183 --> 00:21:31,723
You can live up to your title now.

434
00:21:32,353 --> 00:21:33,353
Of course.

435
00:21:33,483 --> 00:21:35,653
That's why I've been trying
to be more responsible...

436
00:21:35,723 --> 00:21:37,083
and focused at work.

437
00:21:37,583 --> 00:21:38,683
You just watch.

438
00:21:38,853 --> 00:21:40,293
I'll show everyone.

439
00:21:40,383 --> 00:21:41,553
That's not what I meant.

440
00:21:41,923 --> 00:21:44,483
I'm telling you to rebuild your life.

441
00:21:44,553 --> 00:21:46,823
Forget the past and make an honest living.

442
00:21:48,353 --> 00:21:49,553
Don't forget.

443
00:21:49,883 --> 00:21:52,983
This is your chance to show Hyun
Ji what an amazing dad you are.

444
00:21:53,083 --> 00:21:54,483
I got it.

445
00:21:54,883 --> 00:21:57,483
I'll take care of it all.

446
00:21:57,683 --> 00:21:58,723
Do Kyung,

447
00:21:58,953 --> 00:22:00,583
you're my wife.

448
00:22:01,183 --> 00:22:02,383
Take charge...

449
00:22:02,683 --> 00:22:04,083
and do what you want to do.

450
00:22:07,383 --> 00:22:08,383
The time has come...

451
00:22:08,953 --> 00:22:11,183
for us to spread our wings.

452
00:22:13,353 --> 00:22:14,383
(Soo Min's Kimchi Fried Rice)

453
00:22:14,453 --> 00:22:15,533
- Are you all right? - Yes.

454
00:22:16,583 --> 00:22:18,083
Welcome, welcome.

455
00:22:18,123 --> 00:22:19,523
Do you want some kimchi fried rice?

456
00:22:22,383 --> 00:22:23,383
Oh.

457
00:22:23,883 --> 00:22:25,583
You were here before, weren't you?

458
00:22:25,653 --> 00:22:26,883
What's the problem?

459
00:22:26,983 --> 00:22:29,083
I told you, didn't I?

460
00:22:29,483 --> 00:22:31,183
I didn't believe you, but you were right.

461
00:22:31,723 --> 00:22:34,353
When will you ever stop bothering us?

462
00:22:34,883 --> 00:22:36,553
I'm not sure what you mean.

463
00:22:36,623 --> 00:22:38,183
Are you running your own business...

464
00:22:38,253 --> 00:22:40,483
in front of our shops
because we won't leave?

465
00:22:40,553 --> 00:22:42,983
I'm not sure I follow what you say.

466
00:22:43,083 --> 00:22:46,653
We know that you are the head
of the gangsters at Choongshim.

467
00:22:47,983 --> 00:22:50,753
Excuse me, there must
be a misunderstanding.

468
00:22:50,823 --> 00:22:52,983
My husband has nothing to
do with them any more.

469
00:22:53,253 --> 00:22:55,253
Do you think we'll fall for that?

470
00:22:55,283 --> 00:22:56,653
You don't remember me, do you?

471
00:22:57,083 --> 00:23:00,183
Or did you do this to so many
people that you can't remember?

472
00:23:01,123 --> 00:23:02,283
Do you know me?

473
00:23:02,753 --> 00:23:04,873
- Where did you see me?
- Do you really not remember?

474
00:23:05,553 --> 00:23:06,983
Because of you, my dad...

475
00:23:07,083 --> 00:23:08,083
Stop it.

476
00:23:08,283 --> 00:23:09,623
You're wasting your breath.

477
00:23:10,083 --> 00:23:11,883
No matter what you do,

478
00:23:12,383 --> 00:23:14,083
we won't leave Manbok Shophouse.

479
00:23:14,183 --> 00:23:15,483
This is our home.

480
00:23:15,823 --> 00:23:18,683
We won't let you gangsters
steal it away from us.

481
00:23:18,753 --> 00:23:20,083
Let me make myself clear.

482
00:23:20,653 --> 00:23:22,723
I won't let you do that to me again.

483
00:23:26,083 --> 00:23:27,883
Honey, what's going on?

484
00:23:29,883 --> 00:23:31,723
You stay here for now. I'll be right back.

485
00:23:31,783 --> 00:23:33,283
Where are you going? Honey?

486
00:23:33,883 --> 00:23:35,083
Honey!

487
00:23:46,083 --> 00:23:47,853
I need to be on my way soon.

488
00:23:48,283 --> 00:23:49,583
- Take care. - You too.

489
00:24:01,383 --> 00:24:03,483
- Aren't you cold? - I'm fine.

490
00:24:03,553 --> 00:24:04,553
- Hello. - Hello.

491
00:24:04,623 --> 00:24:06,753
- Thanks for the help.
- No problem. We'll get going.

492
00:24:06,823 --> 00:24:07,943
- I'll see you later. - Bye.

493
00:24:08,183 --> 00:24:09,883
- See you. - It's so cold.

494
00:24:09,983 --> 00:24:11,383
Why did you wait outside?

495
00:24:11,453 --> 00:24:13,353
- It's fine. - Let's go inside.

496
00:24:14,123 --> 00:24:15,383
Be careful.

497
00:24:25,723 --> 00:24:27,183
Customers don't come out when it's so cold.

498
00:24:27,253 --> 00:24:28,283
I know.

499
00:24:32,583 --> 00:24:33,683
(Chul's Snack Bar)

500
00:24:40,683 --> 00:24:42,183
Go inside and stand by the heater.

501
00:24:42,283 --> 00:24:43,283
Okay.

502
00:24:49,883 --> 00:24:51,753
- Welcome. - Welcome.

503
00:24:52,683 --> 00:24:53,983
Who's the owner here?

504
00:24:56,483 --> 00:24:59,083
I'm the owner. What's the matter?

505
00:24:59,183 --> 00:25:00,883
I heard you wouldn't take our alcohol...

506
00:25:00,983 --> 00:25:02,583
because you already signed a
contract with another company.

507
00:25:02,983 --> 00:25:05,553
Yes, they offered a better price.

508
00:25:05,623 --> 00:25:06,623
What?

509
00:25:06,683 --> 00:25:07,723
Then,

510
00:25:08,753 --> 00:25:11,823
how much do you think
our protection fee is?

511
00:25:11,983 --> 00:25:14,283
You already ripped us off for years!

512
00:25:14,723 --> 00:25:16,383
I think it's enough.

513
00:25:16,453 --> 00:25:17,883
What did you just say?

514
00:25:18,253 --> 00:25:21,383
Watch your language, Mister.

515
00:25:21,483 --> 00:25:23,653
Should I make sure you don't
say such a thing again?

516
00:25:23,723 --> 00:25:25,083
Should I?

517
00:25:25,253 --> 00:25:26,283
Please don't do this!

518
00:25:28,183 --> 00:25:29,583
Get off of him.

519
00:25:29,753 --> 00:25:30,883
Dad, are you okay?

520
00:25:30,983 --> 00:25:32,683
I'm fine. Don't call the police.

521
00:25:37,083 --> 00:25:39,623
You're the boss here, right?

522
00:25:39,853 --> 00:25:41,583
Please make them stop!

523
00:25:42,683 --> 00:25:44,083
I think it'd be best for you to leave.

524
00:25:44,183 --> 00:25:45,553
Please.

525
00:25:47,283 --> 00:25:48,723
You jerk!

526
00:25:49,453 --> 00:25:50,483
Look here, Kid.

527
00:25:50,853 --> 00:25:53,183
You shouldn't talk like
that to your elders.

528
00:25:53,283 --> 00:25:54,883
Don't touch my son!

529
00:25:54,983 --> 00:25:56,123
You asked for this.

530
00:25:57,683 --> 00:25:58,953
Dad!

531
00:25:59,823 --> 00:26:01,083
Are you all right?

532
00:26:02,183 --> 00:26:04,453
Let's make sure this doesn't happen again.

533
